<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> Try It Yourself </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      input:in-range {
         color: green;
         border: 2px solid green;
      }
      input:out-of-range {
         color: red;
         border: 2px solid red;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p>The <b>:in-range</b> CSS pseudo-class represents an <b>&lt;input&gt;</b> element whose current value is within the range limits specified by the <b>min</b> and <b>max</b> attributes. </p>
   
   <h3> Example: </h3>
   <form action="#">
      <input type="number" min="10" max="20" />
   </form>
   <p> If the value is 10, 20 or between them the <b>&lt;input&gt;</b> element turns green otherwise red. </p>
</body>
</html>